<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_4ad2342e-88e1-4e21-9aae-3757dee05b28" outputclass="ncc-clause" variation="NSW"><sptc>B3D3</sptc><title id="_0c8e0bed-8dea-4d2d-a9e8-0acdbab3e611">General requirements</title><archive-num>2019: NSW B3.3</archive-num><subclause id="_7a022807-a6d2-467e-8335-dc09947524de" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_fa8dd5b7-5981-43ba-b4ba-d47312c58a67">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>A <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1378_4.3.0.xml#_cfc4fec0-3cb7-41d6-b176-4a92d4cdb221" id="_178706d7-0d0f-4158-95e2-9da7986fb248" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">non-drinking water</xref> service must be in accordance with AS/NZS 3500.1, with the following additions to clause 10.3— </p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_504d679a-75e1-47a1-a9b2-5adbc0b0567e">Clause 10.3(d): Top up from a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1250_0.7.0.xml#_762d6a54-e28c-400b-b9c5-5fceac019a05" id="_003cbcd7-e4fd-433f-a49b-508d77aba676" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">drinking water</xref> supply shall be by an indirect trickle top up with a visible air gap external to the tank.</li><li id="_4df55d88-0009-4d88-895f-811b1462c1bd">10.3(e): There shall be no connection between treated greywater systems and <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1250_0.7.0.xml#_762d6a54-e28c-400b-b9c5-5fceac019a05" id="_18231343-9ba3-4f6f-85df-d170c72a8b46" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">drinking water</xref>, rainwater or other sources of supply.</li></ol></subclause></clause>